join Sterling left
Sterling (Sad): Fini. You promised we would do this together. You promised you would help me.
join Fini right
Fini (Sad): I’m sorry, Sterling. This responsibility… it’s not for you. A centralized system controlling the core is too dangerous.
Sterling (Angry): So that’s it? You spend a few years with them, and you choose that human over your own kind? Over me?
Fini (Sad): It’s not about choosing sides! I just can’t risk the core falling into the wrong hands—any hands!
Sterling (Sad): I always looked up to you… Sister… I thought we were eternal.
Sterling (Sad): If this is your choice… then you stand alone.
